    {
      "para_id": "Q001431.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) Enlil spoke : He gave all ... to Šar-kali-šarri , the powerful king , cup-bearer of Enlil , king of Akkad , king of Enlil's people . After he had arrived at the source of the Tigris and the Euphrates , he himself dedicated this ( object ) to Enlil in Nibru ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001431.28",
      "line_range": "28",
      "translation": "(colophon 1, 1) The number of its ( lines ) is six ."
    }
  ],
